{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FF1kuXrHnnWBt4KCdyZ7Bs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the startup sequence, but the log stopped before the discovery phase's \"master not discovered\" error. Let me check for more recent logs or see if the pods are stuck waiting to discover a master.\n\nThe key issue is clear from the configmap: `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is missing. For Elasticsearch 7.x, when a fresh cluster starts for the first time (no existing state), nodes need `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to know which nodes are eligible to vote in the initial master election.\n\nThe fix plan:\n1. **Phase 1: Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap** - this tells the cluster which nodes can bootstrap the master election\n2. **Restart all 3 pods** to force them to pick up the new configuration\n3. **Wait for cluster to form** and verify it's healthy\n4. **Phase 2: Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap** - this setting is only needed for initial bootstrap; leaving it can cause split-brain issues on future restarts\n5. **Do a rolling restart** to remove the bootstrap setting without disrupting the cluster\n6. **Verify the cluster stays healthy** through the rolling restart\n\nLet me check the latest logs to confirm the \"master not discovered\" error.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3101,"cache_read_input_tokens":42317,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3101},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a","uuid":"05d0d006-7305-4abe-9895-a18e9abf159c","request_id":"req_011CcRCp3UE2AFVLoP14h3EL"}
