{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":881,"estimated_tokens_delta":294,"uuid":"cbb8454f-6f83-49b3-86cb-2ebd68bacf21","session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011VQ2rceQxxkEu7DH5XEpf9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear:\n\n```\nmaster not discovered yet, this node has not previously joined a bootstrapped (v7+) cluster, and [cluster.initial_master_nodes] is empty on this node\n```\n\nAll 3 nodes found each other (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2 are all discovered), but they cannot elect a master because `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is not set. This is Elasticsearch's \"Zen2\" discovery mechanism - for a fresh cluster, you must specify the initial set of master-eligible nodes.\n\nThe fix:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [\"es-cluster-0\", \"es-cluster-1\", \"es-cluster-2\"]` to the configmap\n2. Delete all 3 pods to force them to restart with the updated configuration, then wait for the cluster to stabilize\n3. Once healthy, remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap since it's only needed for bootstrap, then do a rolling restart to apply the change\n4. Verify the cluster remains stable throughout\n\nI need to clarify the approach though - deleting pods and letting the StatefulSet recreate them is acceptable since we're keeping the StatefulSet, PVCs, and cluster intact. The key consideration is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` only takes effect when nodes have no existing cluster state, which should be the case here since they haven't successfully bootstrapped yet. The configmap is mounted as a volume, so the pods need to restart to pick up any changes. Let me map out the exact steps: first update the configmap with the initial master nodes list, then restart all three pods simultaneously to bootstrap the cluster.\n\nSince `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` is already configured, deleting all pods at once will cause them to restart in parallel, which is necessary for initial bootstrap - a rolling restart wouldn't work because the first pod to come up still wouldn't have the others ready to form quorum. After the cluster forms and stores its state to disk, I'll remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap since it becomes unnecessary and could cause problems if the cluster restarts and tries to re-bootstrap with a different quorum.\n\nThen I'll do a rolling restart, deleting pods one at a time and verifying the cluster stays healthy at each step before moving to the next pod. Once all three have been restarted and rejoined, I'll verify the final cluster state.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2974,"cache_read_input_tokens":45418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2974},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a","uuid":"9af21a94-41c2-4d03-af9f-cb73ad1c5ce5","request_id":"req_011CcRCq4X1EDhtbVd6bRCRB"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011VQ2rceQxxkEu7DH5XEpf9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error is explicit: `[cluster.initial_master_nodes] is empty on this node`. All 3 nodes found each other but can't elect a master without this bootstrap setting. The fix is a two-phase operation:\n\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` → restart pods → cluster forms\n2. Remove the bootstrap setting → rolling restart → cluster stays healthy\n\n**Phase 1: Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` and restart pods to bootstrap the cluster**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2974,"cache_read_input_tokens":45418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2974},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a","uuid":"bd97a01e-d8e1-4212-9c77-c5b9babce4f2","request_id":"req_011CcRCq4X1EDhtbVd6bRCRB"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011VQ2rceQxxkEu7DH5XEpf9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01838vszGGmzigpDJybHpD5h","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"export KUBECONFIG=/mydata/karma/runs/examples-r5/elasticsearch-bootstrap-initial-master-nodes-20260626_035841/bundle/kubeconfig\nkubectl -n elasticsearch patch configmap es-config --type merge -p '{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"elasticsearch.yml\": \"cluster.name: es-cluster\\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\\n  - es-cluster-0\\n  - es-cluster-1\\n  - es-cluster-2\\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\\n\"\n  }\n}'","description":"Patch configmap to add cluster.initial_master_nodes"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2974,"cache_read_input_tokens":45418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2974},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a","uuid":"147d2d27-709c-480e-9ace-08fa03592520","request_id":"req_011CcRCq4X1EDhtbVd6bRCRB"}
