{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SHj16yFrsidcP56FuAWvhC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is now GREEN with 3 nodes! Now I need to proceed with Phase 2:\n1. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap\n2. Do a rolling restart to ensure the config without the bootstrap setting is picked up\n\nThe `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting is bootstrap-only - it's used only when a node has never joined a cluster before. Once the cluster is formed and nodes have cluster state on disk, this setting is no longer needed. Leaving it in place is actually problematic because if all nodes restart simultaneously (e.g., on a node crash or after a full cluster restart), and the data directory is somehow lost, ES would try to re-bootstrap from scratch with potentially stale data.\nI'll update the configmap to remove that setting, then perform a rolling restart by deleting each pod one at a time and waiting for it to rejoin the cluster before moving to the next one.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":506,"cache_read_input_tokens":55122,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":506},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a","uuid":"6999d155-5de5-4aa1-b52d-b91cdd5d5f07","request_id":"req_011CcRD3skTzpzafctTSbyRa"}
