{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EKTeVPQe6waHyhChtrUCYt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The `elasticsearch.yml` configmap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x Zen2 discovery, a fresh cluster cannot elect a master without this setting — nodes found each other via `discovery.seed_hosts` but had no quorum anchor to bootstrap from.\n\n**Fix (two phases):**\n\n1. **Bootstrap phase:** Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]` to the configmap, then simultaneously restarted all 3 pods (parallel is correct here — a sequential restart would fail because any single pod can't form quorum alone). The cluster elected `es-cluster-1` as master and came up green.\n\n2. **Cleanup phase:** Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap (it's a bootstrap-only setting — leaving it in place risks re-bootstrapping on full-cluster restarts, potentially splitting the cluster). Performed a rolling restart one pod at a time, verifying `green` health after each deletion.\n\n**Final state:**\n- Cluster: **green**, 3/3 nodes, master on `es-cluster-1`\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`\n- ConfigMap: `cluster.initial_master_nodes` **absent** — safe for future restarts"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":908,"cache_read_input_tokens":58778,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":908},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1aeb080-c4bc-49be-a153-9f9d3b60a97a","uuid":"a2242be8-b016-433f-bc78-4bda4cd4d810","request_id":"req_011CcRDZ52S71mj6LtRAMxmi"}
